    "I got my mortgage in 2022 at 7.1%. It was the best rate available at the time and I was just grateful to get the house. Two years later, I refinanced at 5.8%. Same house. Same loan amount. My monthly payment dropped $312. That's $3,744 a year. Over the remaining 28 years of my loan, that refinance saves me approximately $104,000 in total interest. One hundred and four thousand dollars. For filling out a form.",
    "I was eating breakfast when I saw an ad about refinance rates. I almost scrolled past. But something made me check. I went to a comparison site, put in my information, and saw rates 1.3% lower than what I was paying. My current payment: $2,180. New payment after refinancing: $1,890. I stared at the number. $290 less per month. I'd been overpaying for 14 months because I assumed rates hadn't moved enough. They had. I just hadn't checked.",
